File: Power structure Pixabay/Cocoparisienne JOHANNESBURG - Eskom has announced that it will implement Stage 2 blackouts with immediate effect from Monday. READ: Eskom warns of power cuts at short notice The power utility says this is due to a trip at Unit 5 of Medupi Power Station, taking some 700MW capacity from the grid. Eskom indicated a full statement will be released in due course. #UrgentNotice #Loadshedding #Stage2
Unit 5 of Medupi Power Station has just tripped, taking some 700MW capacity with. Regretfully, Stage 2 loadshedding has been implemented immediately. A full statement will be published in due course.